ospurge/resources/senlin.py.message:
It isn't just one API call, though, to be fair. You have to walk all clusters which the user owns and find which have this policy attached (this is many:1 clusters:policies). The number of API calls could easily explode.

This might be a hack, but what if we just add on to the resources returned in list() so we don't need to cache it on the class? Maybe something like:

    def list(self):
        if not self.cloud.has_service('clustering'):
            return []
        policies = self.find_policies_with_clusters()
        return policies

    def find_policies_with_clusters(self):
        policies = self.cloud.cluster.policies()
        for cluster in self.cloud.cluster.clusters():
            for policy in self.cloud.cluster.\
                    cluster_policies(cluster=cluster.id):
                for policy_obj in policies:
                    if policy_obj.id == policy.policy_id:
                        if not hasattr(policy_obj, 'attached_clusters'):
                            policy_obj.attached_clusters = []
                        policy_obj.attached_clusters.append(cluster.id)
        return policies

